Package ohos.miscservices.download

Class DownloadSession

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.miscservices.download.DownloadSession

  • public class DownloadSession
extends Object
    Defines an HTTP or HTTPS download session as a DownloadSession object and provides management interfaces, such as starting, pausing, resuming, and deleting a session, and querying session details.

    Note that applications must obtain the ohos.permission.INTERNET permission to use the interfaces.

    Since:
    1

    • Method Detail

      • attach

        public boolean attach​(long id)
        Associates a newly created download session with a specified ID.

        Applications should save download session IDs returned by start() to local storage. After the application restarts, create a download session and use this method to associate it with a stored session ID.

        Parameters:
        id - Indicates a download session ID.
        Returns:
        Returns true if the session is associated with the ID; returns false otherwise. The association may fail because the download session does not exist or it has been started.

      • start

        public long start​()
        Starts a download session.

        If the session is successfully started, the session ID is returned. Keep the ID properly. It will be used for the download session after the application restarts.

        The ohos.permission.INTERNET permission is required to use this method.

        Returns:
        Returns the download session ID if the session is started; returns -1 otherwise.
        See Also:
        attach(long)

      • remove

        public boolean remove​()
        Deletes a download session and the downloaded files.
        Returns:
        Returns true if the session is deleted; returns false otherwise.

      • pause

        public boolean pause​()
        Pauses a download session.
        Returns:
        Returns true if the download is paused; returns false otherwise.
        See Also:
        resume()

      • resume

        public boolean resume​()
        Resumes a paused download session.

        Only if the server providing files supports resumable upload, the download session can be resumed.

        Returns:
        Returns true if the download is resumed; returns false otherwise.
        See Also:
        pause()

        public DownloadSession.DownloadInfo query​()
